### Insurance Fraud Detection — Claim Intake API (REST)
### Use with VS Code REST Client or IntelliJ HTTP Client.
### Pipeline runs fully autonomously after submission:
###   submitClaim → StructureClaim → PredictFraud (N models) → EvaluateClaim (M models)
###
### Optional run configuration (multi-model pipeline):
###   predictModels — predict models run in parallel (default: ["sap-rpt-1-large","gbc"])
###   evaluations   — LLMs that evaluate, each paired to ONE prediction (isolated tracks)
###                   default: [{opus ← sap-rpt-1-large}, {gpt-oss-120b ← gbc}]
###   actualFraud   — optional ground-truth label (labeled/demo cases only)
###
### See ./monitor.http for OData queries and ./demo.http for curated Tathergang cases.

@intakeUrl = http://localhost:4004/api/intake

# ─── 1) Minimal submit — default two isolated tracks ─────────────────────────
# predict: sap-rpt-1-large (proprietary) + gbc (custom ML); evaluate: Claude←RPT, OSS←gbc.

POST {{intakeUrl}}/submitClaim
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "externalRef": "INS-2024-AUTO-002",
  "rawText": "Minor fender bender in a supermarket parking lot. Vehicle was lightly bumped. No injuries reported. Estimated repair cost from workshop is approximately USD 1,200. Claim type: auto."
}

###

# ─── 2) Override the run config — compare several models in parallel ─────────
# Three predict models; three evaluators, each consuming a specific prediction
# (isolated tracks): Claude←RPT, gpt-oss-120b←gbc, gemma-3-27b←rf.

POST {{intakeUrl}}/submitClaim
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "externalRef": "INS-2024-AUTO-003",
  "rawText": "Vehicle rear-ended at traffic lights on the highway. Police report filed and a witness gave a statement. Estimated repair cost USD 4,300. Claim type: auto.",
  "predictModels": ["sap-rpt-1-large", "gbc", "rf"],
  "evaluations": [
    { "model": "anthropic--claude-4.6-opus", "inputPredictModel": "sap-rpt-1-large" },
    { "model": "gpt-oss-120b",               "inputPredictModel": "gbc" },
    { "model": "gemma-3-27b",                "inputPredictModel": "rf" }
  ]
}

###

# ─── 3) Submit with a known ground-truth label (predicted-vs-actual) ─────────

POST {{intakeUrl}}/submitClaim
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "externalRef": "INS-2024-PROP-007",
  "rawText": "Claimant reports total loss of all home contents due to a kitchen fire. Estimated loss EUR 75,000. No fire brigade report on file. Claim type: property.",
  "predictModels": ["sap-rpt-1-large", "gbc"],
  "evaluations": [
    { "model": "anthropic--claude-4.6-opus", "inputPredictModel": "sap-rpt-1-large" },
    { "model": "gpt-oss-120b",               "inputPredictModel": "gbc" }
  ],
  "actualFraud": true
}

###

# ─── 4) Submit with an attachment (base64 encoded) ───────────────────────────

POST {{intakeUrl}}/submitClaim
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "externalRef": "INS-2024-AUTO-012",
  "rawText": "Vehicle rear-ended at traffic lights on highway. Police report filed. Estimated repair cost USD 4,300. Claim type: auto.",
  "attachments": [
    {
      "filename": "police_report.txt",
      "mediaType": "text/plain",
      "content": "UG9saWNlIFJlcG9ydDogSW5jaWRlbnQgb24gSGlnaHdheS4gVmVoaWNsZSAxIHJlYXItZW5kZWQgVmVoaWNsZSAyIGF0IHRyYWZmaWMgbGlnaHRzLiBObyBpbmp1cmllcy4="
    }
  ]
}

